{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":167,"text":"Recently I visited Beloit, Wisconsin."},{"time":3181,"text":"And I was there to honor a great 20th century explorer,"},{"time":6829,"text":"Roy Chapman Andrews."},{"time":8871,"text":"During his time at the American Museum of Natural History,"},{"time":11715,"text":"Andrews led a range of expeditions to uncharted regions,"},{"time":15815,"text":"like here in the Gobi Desert."},{"time":17550,"text":"He was quite a figure."},{"time":18958,"text":"He was later, it's said, the basis of the Indiana Jones character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22632,"text":"And when I was in Beloit, Wisconsin,"},{"time":24829,"text":"I gave a public lecture to a group of middle school students."},{"time":28962,"text":"And I'm here to tell you,"},{"time":30531,"text":"if there's anything more intimidating than talking here at TED,"},{"time":33235,"text":"it'll be trying to hold the attention"},{"time":35067,"text":"of a group of a thousand 12-year-olds for a 45-minute lecture."},{"time":38960,"text":"Don't try that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40839,"text":"At the end of the lecture they asked a number of questions,"},{"time":44381,"text":"but there was one that's really stuck with me since then."},{"time":47683,"text":"There was a young girl who stood up,"},{"time":49600,"text":"and she asked the question:"},{"time":50931,"text":"\"Where should we explore?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":52979,"text":"I think there's a sense that many of us have"},{"time":55110,"text":"that the great age of exploration on Earth is over,"},{"time":57929,"text":"that for the next generation"},{"time":59461,"text":"they're going to have to go to outer space or the deepest oceans"},{"time":62879,"text":"in order to find something significant to explore."},{"time":65429,"text":"But is that really the case?"},{"time":67929,"text":"Is there really nowhere significant for us to explore"},{"time":70925,"text":"left here on Earth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72650,"text":"It sort of made me think back"},{"time":73833,"text":"to one of my favorite explorers in the history of biology."},{"time":76583,"text":"This is an explorer of the unseen world, Martinus Beijerinck."},{"time":79917,"text":"So Beijerinck set out to discover the cause"},{"time":82375,"text":"of tobacco mosaic disease."},{"time":84740,"text":"What he did is he took the infected juice from tobacco plants"},{"time":88292,"text":"and he would filter it through smaller and smaller filters."},{"time":91229,"text":"And he reached the point"},{"time":92795,"text":"where he felt that there must be something out there"},{"time":95806,"text":"that was smaller than the smallest forms of life that were ever known --"},{"time":99250,"text":"bacteria, at the time."},{"time":101294,"text":"He came up with a name for his mystery agent."},{"time":104682,"text":"He called it the virus --"},{"time":106708,"text":"Latin for \"poison.\""},{"time":108983,"text":"And in uncovering viruses,"},{"time":111760,"text":"Beijerinck really opened this entirely new world for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115381,"text":"We now know that viruses make up the majority"},{"time":117375,"text":"of the genetic information on our planet,"},{"time":119667,"text":"more than the genetic information"},{"time":121333,"text":"of all other forms of life combined."},{"time":123083,"text":"And obviously there's been tremendous practical applications"},{"time":126177,"text":"associated with this world --"},{"time":127431,"text":"things like the eradication of smallpox,"},{"time":129833,"text":"the advent of a vaccine against cervical cancer,"},{"time":133488,"text":"which we now know is mostly caused by human papillomavirus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137087,"text":"And Beijerinck's discovery,"},{"time":138760,"text":"this was not something that occurred 500 years ago."},{"time":141481,"text":"It was a little over 100 years ago"},{"time":144160,"text":"that Beijerinck discovered viruses."},{"time":146580,"text":"So basically we had automobiles,"},{"time":148467,"text":"but we were unaware of the forms of life"},{"time":150710,"text":"that make up most of the genetic information on our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153716,"text":"We now have these amazing tools"},{"time":155898,"text":"to allow us to explore the unseen world --"},{"time":158208,"text":"things like deep sequencing,"},{"time":160221,"text":"which allow us to do much more than just skim the surface"},{"time":163785,"text":"and look at individual genomes from a particular species,"},{"time":166875,"text":"but to look at entire metagenomes,"},{"time":169370,"text":"the communities of teeming microorganisms in, on and around us"},{"time":173550,"text":"and to document all of the genetic information in these species."},{"time":177071,"text":"We can apply these techniques"},{"time":178542,"text":"to things from soil to skin and everything in between."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183052,"text":"In my organization we now do this on a regular basis"},{"time":186042,"text":"to identify the causes of outbreaks"},{"time":188421,"text":"that are unclear exactly what causes them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191710,"text":"And just to give you a sense of how this works,"},{"time":194042,"text":"imagine that we took a nasal swab from every single one of you."},{"time":197042,"text":"And this is something we commonly do"},{"time":198404,"text":"to look for respiratory viruses like influenza."},{"time":201398,"text":"The first thing we would see"},{"time":203250,"text":"is a tremendous amount of genetic information."},{"time":206300,"text":"And if we started looking into that genetic information,"},{"time":208708,"text":"we'd see a number of usual suspects out there --"},{"time":211043,"text":"of course, a lot of human genetic information,"},{"time":212836,"text":"but also bacterial and viral information,"},{"time":215708,"text":"mostly from things that are completely harmless within your nose."},{"time":218875,"text":"But we'd also see something very, very surprising."},{"time":221787,"text":"As we started to look at this information,"},{"time":223862,"text":"we would see that about 20 percent of the genetic information in your nose"},{"time":228208,"text":"doesn't match anything that we've ever seen before --"},{"time":231125,"text":"no plant, animal, fungus, virus or bacteria."},{"time":234296,"text":"Basically we have no clue what this is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237800,"text":"And for the small group of us who actually study this kind of data,"},{"time":241920,"text":"a few of us have actually begun to call this information"},{"time":245635,"text":"biological dark matter."},{"time":248037,"text":"We know it's not anything that we've seen before;"},{"time":250985,"text":"it's sort of the equivalent of an uncharted continent"},{"time":254092,"text":"right within our own genetic information."},{"time":256810,"text":"And there's a lot of it."},{"time":258187,"text":"If you think 20 percent of genetic information in your nose is a lot"},{"time":261673,"text":"of biological dark matter,"},{"time":263292,"text":"if we looked at your gut,"},{"time":265042,"text":"up to 40 or 50 percent of that information is biological dark matter."},{"time":268738,"text":"And even in the relatively sterile blood,"},{"time":270977,"text":"around one to two percent of this information is dark matter --"},{"time":273958,"text":"can't be classified, can't be typed or matched with anything we've seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278706,"text":"At first we thought that perhaps this was artifact."},{"time":281333,"text":"These deep sequencing tools are relatively new."},{"time":284585,"text":"But as they become more and more accurate,"},{"time":286658,"text":"we've determined that this information is a form of life,"},{"time":290246,"text":"or at least some of it is a form of life."},{"time":292833,"text":"And while the hypotheses for explaining the existence of biological dark matter"},{"time":297198,"text":"are really only in their infancy,"},{"time":299136,"text":"there's a very, very exciting possibility that exists:"},{"time":302813,"text":"that buried in this life, in this genetic information,"},{"time":306292,"text":"are signatures of as of yet unidentified life."},{"time":310780,"text":"That as we explore these strings of A's, T's, C's and G's,"},{"time":314715,"text":"we may uncover a completely new class of life"},{"time":318050,"text":"that, like Beijerinck, will fundamentally change"},{"time":320462,"text":"the way that we think about the nature of biology."},{"time":322658,"text":"That perhaps will allow us to identify the cause of a cancer that afflicts us"},{"time":327087,"text":"or identify the source of an outbreak that we aren't familiar with"},{"time":330619,"text":"or perhaps create a new tool in molecular biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333513,"text":"I'm pleased to announce that,"},{"time":335198,"text":"along with colleagues at Stanford and Caltech and UCSF,"},{"time":340140,"text":"we're currently starting an initiative"},{"time":341779,"text":"to explore biological dark matter for the existence of new forms of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345752,"text":"A little over a hundred years ago,"},{"time":347896,"text":"people were unaware of viruses,"},{"time":350600,"text":"the forms of life that make up most of the genetic information on our planet."},{"time":354839,"text":"A hundred years from now, people may marvel"},{"time":357421,"text":"that we were perhaps completely unaware of a new class of life"},{"time":360875,"text":"that literally was right under our noses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364179,"text":"It's true, we may have charted all the continents on the planet"},{"time":367502,"text":"and we may have discovered all the mammals that are out there,"},{"time":370583,"text":"but that doesn't mean that there's nothing left to explore on Earth."},{"time":374139,"text":"Beijerinck and his kind"},{"time":376144,"text":"provide an important lesson for the next generation of explorers --"},{"time":379831,"text":"people like that young girl from Beloit, Wisconsin."},{"time":383163,"text":"And I think if we phrase that lesson, it's something like this:"},{"time":386958,"text":"Don't assume that what we currently think is out there is the full story."},{"time":391187,"text":"Go after the dark matter in whatever field you choose to explore."},{"time":396250,"text":"There are unknowns all around us"},{"time":398369,"text":"and they're just waiting to be discovered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400750,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402419,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}